with you right now.

19
00:01:03,605 --> 00:01:05,732
And that...

20
00:01:05,899 --> 00:01:07,776
...would be...

21
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:10,654
...a toast.

22
00:01:11,780 --> 00:01:13,699
A toast to your new merger.

23
00:01:15,242 --> 00:01:18,203
Pheebs, could you help me?
With the cobbler?

24
00:01:23,083 --> 00:01:25,294
Am I missing something?

25
00:01:26,628 --> 00:01:28,630
Okay, that was a three-course meal,

26
00:01:28,797 --> 00:01:32,593
not including the fruit and cheese
plate. I gave you a million openings.

27
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:34,344
What do you want, a drumroll?

28
00:01:34,553 --> 00:01:36,638
Actually, that's not a bad idea.

29
00:01:36,805 --> 00:01:38,974
You are going with him
to France tomorrow.

30
00:01:39,141 --> 00:01:42,102
You've put this off for too long.
You have to tell him you're a witch.

31
00:01:42,269 --> 00:01:43,937
I just think maybe
we should wait until

32
00:01:44,521 --> 00:01:46,064
we get there to tell him, you know?

33
00:01:46,231 --> 00:01:48,692
Then if there's an emergency,
you can orb us back, okay?

34
00:01:48,901 --> 00:01:51,820
You've probably been caught
almost like a million times.

35
00:01:51,987 --> 00:01:53,822
You can't keep taking that risk.

36
00:01:53,989 --> 00:01:55,657
I know.

37
00:01:56,450 --> 00:01:57,993
Maybe I should wait till tomorrow,

38
00:01:58,160 --> 00:02:00,996
until after the big banquet
so I don't upset his big day.

39
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:04,166
I think that you have a big
problem with avoiding conflict,

40
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:07,294
and one day, missy, it is gonna
come back and bite you in the ass.

41
00:02:07,836 --> 00:02:09,713
Hey, he's getting
a little antsy in there.

42
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:12,341
And you, what is it
with this whole karma thing?

43
00:02:12,508 --> 00:02:14,718
You're supposed to be
making it easier for her.

44
00:02:17,054 --> 00:02:18,430
Piper needs your help fast.

45
00:02:18,597 --> 00:02:20,933
Saved by the orb, great.
Keep Jason occupied.

46
00:02:27,064 --> 00:02:28,774
Leo?

47
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:30,776
What are you doing here?

48
00:02:30,984 --> 00:02:33,153
Just bringing dessert,
you want some?

49
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:35,364
The girls are just tidying up.

50
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:40,536
Crap.

51
00:02:43,372 --> 00:02:46,166
- Piper.
- About time.

52
00:02:49,127 --> 00:02:50,963
It wasn't easy to find you
in these catacombs.

53
00:02:51,129 --> 00:02:52,798
You were supposed to wait
so I could help.

54
00:02:52,965 --> 00:02:54,550
Well, I thought I could handle it.

55
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:56,927
Except I must have
missed something in the Book.

56
00:02:57,135 --> 00:02:59,721
- I guess so.
- Look, every time I hit one,

57
00:02:59,888 --> 00:03:01,682
two more show up.

58
00:03:09,273 --> 00:03:11,233
Okay, back up.

59
00:03:11,692 --> 00:03:13,318
Hey, boys.

60
00:03:24,246 --> 00:03:27,040
Okay, new plan. Blast and then bail.

61
00:03:27,207 --> 00:03:28,834
Okay.

62
00:03:29,042 --> 00:03:32,045
Hey, Phoebe,
what's taking you so long?

63
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:33,881
Where...? Where did they go?

64
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:36,508
Must be an emergency
or something.

65
00:03:36,717 --> 00:03:39,678
It's always some emergency
or some phone call

66
00:03:39,887 --> 00:03:42,931
or some marathon pee break.
What's going on?

67
00:05:37,838 --> 00:05:40,507
I think I'd better go check on Wyatt.

68
00:05:42,176 --> 00:05:44,052
I've never seen him like that.
He looked at me

69
00:05:44,219 --> 00:05:45,470
like he had no idea who I was.

70
00:05:45,637 --> 00:05:48,849
He doesn't know you.
Not the witch you anyway.

71
00:05:49,266 --> 00:05:51,768
He's just gonna need some time.

72
00:05:51,935 --> 00:05:55,439
Why didn't I just tell him?
And no "I told you so's."

73
00:05:55,606 --> 00:05:57,733
We all make little mistakes, honey.

74
00:05:57,941 --> 00:05:59,443
This was a very big mistake.

75
00:05:59,610 --> 00:06:02,362
I can't imagine how he's feeling
right now, what he's going through.

76
00:06:02,529 --> 00:06:05,115
The good news is,
it's out in the open now

77
00:06:05,282 --> 00:06:07,701
and, you know, you guys
have no more secrets.

78
00:06:07,868 --> 00:06:11,246
Food's away, table's cleared.
There anything else I can do?

79
00:06:11,413 --> 00:06:13,373
No, thank you.

80
00:06:13,582 --> 00:06:16,293
Hey, I feel awful.
Sorry about what happened.

81
00:06:16,502 --> 00:06:17,920
It's not your fault.

82
00:06:18,462 --> 00:06:20,714
Well... Well, actually it is.

83
00:06:20,923 --> 00:06:23,550
Why? Did you shove Jason
into the kitchen?

84
00:06:23,717 --> 00:06:25,761
No, but my karma did.

85
00:06:27,012 --> 00:06:30,849
I'm serious. I'm convinced I'm carrying
the burden of my family's karma.

86
00:06:31,016 --> 00:06:33,685
I mean, we did so much bad
with magic.

87
00:06:33,852 --> 00:06:37,814
Now magic's doing bad to me.
And those I care about.

88
00:06:37,981 --> 00:06:40,859
Now, that is completely ridiculous.

89
00:06:41,485 --> 00:06:44,446
The feud has lasted
for decades in my family

90
00:06:44,655 --> 00:06:46,657
and so many people
were hurt in the crossfire.

91
00:06:46,823 --> 00:06:49,451
I mean, somebody's gotta
inherit that bad karma, right?

92
00:06:50,494 --> 00:06:52,246
That's not really how karma works.

93
00:06:52,454 --> 00:06:54,748
You live a double life
with your boyfriend,

94
00:06:54,957 --> 00:06:59,002
and you pay the price. If anyone's
karma made this happen, it's mine.

95
00:06:59,211 --> 00:07:02,548
That's true. You had the chance
to clean this up tonight, and you didn't.

96
00:07:02,756 --> 00:07:04,299
See, there's that
"I told you so," huh?

97
00:07:04,508 --> 00:07:06,468
Only to make a point.

98
00:07:06,677 --> 00:07:10,848
No, you're right. I've been
avoiding conflict my whole life.

99
00:07:11,056 --> 00:07:13,559
What, and it just happened
the night I was here? I mean,

100
00:07:13,725 --> 00:07:15,352
- that's all I'm saying.
- You guys,

101
00:07:15,519 --> 00:07:19,523
this mea culpa game is real fun and all,
but we're not gonna solve anything.

102
00:07:19,690 --> 00:07:22,109
Those multiplying swarm demons
on the other hand?

103
00:07:22,276 --> 00:07:23,777
Right, we riled them up, didn't we?

104
00:07:23,944 --> 00:07:26,697
And if they attack right now,
we won't know how to deal with them.

105
00:07:26,864 --> 00:07:31,034
So why don't you two hit the Book
and I'll catch up after I check on Wyatt.

106
00:07:31,201 --> 00:07:33,537
Would you guys mind
if I sat this one out?

107
00:07:33,704 --> 00:07:35,747
I kind of feel like
I need to go see Jason.

108
00:07:35,914 --> 00:07:40,210
- Well, maybe after we've...
- No, we can handle it.

109
00:07:42,087 --> 00:07:44,506
All right.

110
00:07:47,759 --> 00:07:49,428
Leo. No, no, no.

111
00:07:49,595 --> 00:07:51,180
What? What, what, what is it?

112
00:07:51,346 --> 00:07:52,806
This, this.

113
00:07:52,973 --> 00:07:54,224
What, my grandmother's quilt?

114
00:07:54,391 --> 00:07:58,854
Her red quilt, the colour of anger
and violence and all things bad.

115
00:07:59,062 --> 00:08:01,940
- Bad? I used that quilt.
- Well, you can have it back.

116
00:08:02,107 --> 00:08:06,445
Wyatt is now using
the powder-blue baby blanket.

117
00:08:06,612 --> 00:08:09,031
Did you turn off
the serenity Mozart CD?

118
00:08:12,326 --> 00:08:15,204
Look, we need to bathe Wyatt
in goodness,

119
00:08:15,370 --> 00:08:18,582
and nurture peace
and serenity, happy things.

120
00:08:19,082 --> 00:08:22,169
Piper, don't you think you're
overreacting a little bit?

121
00:08:22,377 --> 00:08:24,796
Leo, there is no such thing
as overreacting

122
00:08:24,963 --> 00:08:26,965
when it comes
to the future of our child.

123
00:08:27,132 --> 00:08:30,093
Okay, but aren't the swarm demons
the last on the list of threats?

124
00:08:30,302 --> 00:08:32,721
- Yes, but...
- Okay, and when they're gone,

125
00:08:32,888 --> 00:08:34,806
are you gonna stop
worrying a little bit?

126
00:08:34,973 --> 00:08:39,353
No, because I sent Chris to suss out
if there's any new threats.

127
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:43,065
Okay, not to press a point,
but didn't you just have an epiphany

128
00:08:43,232 --> 00:08:45,651
about not focusing all
of your energy on Wyatt?

129
00:08:45,817 --> 00:08:48,111
Yes, well, that was before
Chris informed us

130
00:08:48,278 --> 00:08:51,365
that our child was gonna grow up
to be the future of all evil.

131
00:08:53,283 --> 00:08:58,747
Besides, it's not all I do.
I have the club, I have friends.

132
00:08:59,331 --> 00:09:00,582
Well...

133
00:09:01,542 --> 00:09:05,128
Look, it's just that
Wyatt still comes first.

134
00:09:05,295 --> 00:09:09,174
Which is why you are gonna
take him up to the Elders

135
00:09:09,341 --> 00:09:12,928
so he's safe while we figure out
how to deal with the swarm demons.

136
00:09:13,095 --> 00:09:15,180
While you're there,
ask them if there's anything

137
00:09:15,347 --> 00:09:17,391
they can do to ensure
goodness in Wyatt.

138
00:09:17,558 --> 00:09:20,686
- You know, pull a few strings?
- Piper, we don't need strings pulled,

139
00:09:20,853 --> 00:09:22,437
we can protect our son ourselves.

140
00:09:22,646 --> 00:09:25,440
Well, in the future,
apparently, we don't.

141
00:09:25,607 --> 00:09:28,944
Okay, so look, there are blue bootees
in the bag in case he gets cold.

142
00:09:29,111 --> 00:09:31,738
So don't be afraid
to use them, okay?

143
00:09:35,826 --> 00:09:39,371
Don't ask me, she's your mother.

144
00:09:41,707 --> 00:09:45,878
Look, you and I both know,
in order to make this work,

145
00:09:46,044 --> 00:09:49,339
- you can't repress yourself.
- I'm not. Look, practising magic.

146
00:09:49,506 --> 00:09:51,508
Yeah, but you don't want me to.

147
00:09:51,717 --> 00:09:54,386
Every relationship is gonna
have its challenges, right?

148
00:09:54,553 --> 00:09:57,764
- Look at Phoebe and Jason.
- I'm telling you, that was me.

149
00:09:57,973 --> 00:10:00,976
No, that was them not being
truthful with each other.

150
00:10:01,143 --> 00:10:03,812
And as long as we are,
we're gonna be fine.

151
00:10:04,730 --> 00:10:07,774
"Fine" would be if I could
start over with a clean slate.

152
00:10:07,941 --> 00:10:10,319
You just be the wonderful person
that you are,

153
00:10:10,485 --> 00:10:13,530
and it's gonna make up for all the
bad things that your family ever did.

154
00:10:13,822 --> 00:10:16,283
Not in this lifetime.
I want to start over.

155
00:10:16,491 --> 00:10:19,828
It's not possible.
If it were, everybody would do it.

156
00:10:20,037 --> 00:10:22,247
Okay, everybody's
not a powerful witch.

157
00:10:22,456 --> 00:10:25,542
Look, karma is the DNA
of the universe.

158
00:10:25,709 --> 00:10:28,337
It's what balances everything out.
You start screwing with that,

159
00:10:28,504 --> 00:10:31,507
you can mess up
the entire cosmic order of things.

160
00:10:32,633 --> 00:10:34,968
Maybe you can help me cast a spell.

161
00:10:35,177 --> 00:10:37,346
What part of "no shortcuts"
are you not getting?

162
00:10:37,679 --> 00:10:41,600
There's an aura cleanse, a chakra
cleanse, but no karma cleanse.

163
00:10:41,767 --> 00:10:45,229
If it were possible to be cleansed,
it'd be in there, but there's no spell.

164
00:10:45,395 --> 00:10:47,272
It can't be done.

165
00:10:47,856 --> 00:10:50,609
- Got anything?
- Yeah, let's see,

166
00:10:50,776 --> 00:10:54,071
they are distant relatives
of Quossis and vampires,

167
00:10:54,238 --> 00:10:55,864
which means
they come from a hive.

168
00:10:56,615 --> 00:10:58,242
Did you even read this?

169
00:10:58,408 --> 00:11:00,369
I skimmed it.

170
00:11:00,577 --> 00:11:03,539
So they were drones
that we were killing.

171
00:11:03,747 --> 00:11:06,750
Well, no wonder
they just kept coming back.

172
00:11:06,959 --> 00:11:09,670
It says we have to kill the king
to kill the hive,

173
00:11:09,837 --> 00:11:12,881
which requires the power-of-three
spell. I'll call Phoebe.

174
00:11:13,048 --> 00:11:15,926
Hey, just slow down
there, okay? Take it easy.

175
00:11:16,677 --> 00:11:21,682
Okay, you orb out and get Phoebe,
and I'll start on the potion.

176
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:24,935
Why don't we just track
the leader down? You and I.

177
00:11:25,102 --> 00:11:27,938
That way, Phoebe and Jason can
have a little bit of time alone, yeah?

178
00:11:28,605 --> 00:11:32,734
Well, what if the swarm
attacks before...? Okay, fine.

179
00:11:32,901 --> 00:11:34,778
We'll locate the ruler first.

180
00:11:34,987 --> 00:11:36,780
Brilliant idea.

181
00:11:37,573 --> 00:11:40,284
Hey, can I orb you anywhere?

182
00:11:40,492 --> 00:11:43,328
No, it's okay. I drove my car here.

183
00:11:43,537 --> 00:11:45,289
Okay. I'll see you soon.

184
00:12:19,948 --> 00:12:21,825
- You stay away.
- We need to talk.

185
00:12:22,034 --> 00:12:24,161
No. No. I don't want to talk.

186
00:12:24,369 --> 00:12:25,913
You're... This is your...

187
00:12:27,039 --> 00:12:29,791
This... This is so beyond...

188
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:33,045
This is so far beyond my reality.

189
00:12:33,253 --> 00:12:37,382
You know, l... I'm just still trying
to figure out how

190
00:12:37,549 --> 00:12:40,761
you could...
Fifteen months, I didn't know!

191
00:12:40,969 --> 00:12:42,971
I wanted to tell you.

192
00:12:43,138 --> 00:12:45,307
I really did, but I couldn't.

193
00:12:45,474 --> 00:12:47,851
And you know now,
so can we talk about this, please?

194
00:12:48,018 --> 00:12:49,811
Okay, fine, let's talk.

195
00:12:49,978 --> 00:12:54,525
All right, what...? What was this, huh?
The Godiva girls, was that magic?

196
00:12:54,691 --> 00:12:56,527
- Yeah.
- Man, still...

197
00:12:56,777 --> 00:13:00,572
Okay, what about that funny-looking
little cousin of yours, cousin Shamus,

198
00:13:00,739 --> 00:13:03,116
what the hell was he?
One of the seven dwarves?

199
00:13:03,283 --> 00:13:06,370
No, actually, he was a leprechaun.

200
00:13:06,537 --> 00:13:07,996
Not really my cousin.

201
00:13:10,749 --> 00:13:12,626
Look, Jason, I know how you feel.

202
00:13:12,835 --> 00:13:14,920
How do I feel, Phoebe?

203
00:13:15,671 --> 00:13:18,632
Tell me because...
Because I don't know.

204
00:13:18,799 --> 00:13:20,843
But you, you always seem to know.

205
00:13:21,009 --> 00:13:23,387
So tell me, how's it
gonna feel when I crash,

206
00:13:23,554 --> 00:13:25,597
because I see one coming.

207
00:13:25,806 --> 00:13:28,433
Is it gonna feel like
when you said, "I love you too"?

208
00:13:28,851 --> 00:13:31,520
Because that,
that was magic, wasn't it?

209
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:34,982
But I do love you.

210
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:40,529
I don't...
I don't have time for this.

211
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:44,449
I didn't want you
to find out like this, believe me.

212
00:13:45,158 --> 00:13:46,743
I...

213
00:13:46,910 --> 00:13:50,706
I have to concentrate. I'm speaking
in front of 100 shareholders

214
00:13:50,873 --> 00:13:55,836
celebrating the second-biggest
French media merger of the decade.

215
00:13:56,003 --> 00:13:57,629
Okay?

216
00:13:57,796 --> 00:14:00,090
So...

217
00:14:00,257 --> 00:14:02,676
...I need to be in focus.

218
00:14:05,971 --> 00:14:07,472
You're the one that wanted to look

219
00:14:07,639 --> 00:14:10,100
for the swarm king
in the first place, remember?

220
00:14:10,267 --> 00:14:14,688
Yeah, that's when we thought
it was a hive, not so much of a maze.

221
00:14:14,855 --> 00:14:18,275
Oh, no. Is this starting to look familiar?

222
00:14:18,442 --> 00:14:21,069
- Are we?
- Going around in circles?

223
00:14:21,403 --> 00:14:23,906
- Great.
- Let's just orb home.

224
00:14:24,072 --> 00:14:27,576
Why are you in such a rush
to go home all of a sudden?

225
00:14:27,826 --> 00:14:32,706
It's Richard. Any time he's alone for
too long, bad things start to happen.

226
00:14:33,916 --> 00:14:35,542
No!

227
00:14:37,377 --> 00:14:39,630
That only attracts them more,
remember?

228
00:14:48,597 --> 00:14:50,349
Should we follow them?

229
00:14:50,516 --> 00:14:52,059
Good idea.

230
00:14:57,147 --> 00:14:58,565
- Now?
- Yeah.

231
00:15:29,054 --> 00:15:32,391
"I call to thee, pure witch's fire

232
00:15:32,558 --> 00:15:35,435
Through vortex flow
The heavenly mire

233
00:15:35,602 --> 00:15:38,063
Cleanse brackish karma of debris

234
00:15:38,230 --> 00:15:41,275
From dark to light, sweep history"

235
00:15:59,209 --> 00:16:01,336
Hello, anybody home?

236
00:16:35,579 --> 00:16:38,165
