484
00:31:45,030 --> 00:31:48,826
to turn your one shining
moment into chaos? And to...

485
00:31:48,992 --> 00:31:51,578
...strip in front
of a packed auditorium?

486
00:31:51,745 --> 00:31:53,705
No. Look,

487
00:31:53,872 --> 00:31:56,542
it's not her fault. You want
to blame somebody, blame me.

488
00:31:56,708 --> 00:31:58,752
- I cast a spell that...
- Hold on.

489
00:32:00,504 --> 00:32:02,798
- You too?
- Yeah, look.

490
00:32:02,965 --> 00:32:05,676
There's no time to explain,
just take this, please.

491
00:32:05,843 --> 00:32:07,469
The moment you see
Phoebe, throw this,

492
00:32:07,636 --> 00:32:09,429
she'll be back to normal. I promise.

493
00:32:09,596 --> 00:32:12,307
Wait a second. What is that?

494
00:32:12,641 --> 00:32:14,518
It's a potion.

495
00:32:15,018 --> 00:32:17,896
- Get out of here.
- Look, I screwed up big time, all right?

496
00:32:18,105 --> 00:32:21,817
The only way to fix this
is to use this on Phoebe.

497
00:32:22,484 --> 00:32:23,735
If you love her...

498
00:32:24,820 --> 00:32:26,530
...you'll do it.

499
00:32:33,912 --> 00:32:36,707
Well, if you would just hold still...

500
00:32:37,666 --> 00:32:41,044
Fine. There, you're done.

501
00:32:42,838 --> 00:32:45,048
We wouldn't be in this mess
if it weren't for Phoebe

502
00:32:45,215 --> 00:32:47,676
not being able to deal with conflict.

503
00:32:47,843 --> 00:32:50,512
Actually, we wouldn't be in this mess

504
00:32:50,679 --> 00:32:53,599
if your boyfriend
could handle his magic.

505
00:32:53,932 --> 00:32:55,934
Ow, you did that on purpose.

506
00:32:56,101 --> 00:32:57,269
Yes, I did.

507
00:32:58,729 --> 00:33:01,481
Maybe we should just focus
on how to save Phoebe.

508
00:33:01,648 --> 00:33:04,234
Well, we could storm the hive,
but then again,

509
00:33:04,401 --> 00:33:06,320
she'd probably just
help them stop us.

510
00:33:06,528 --> 00:33:08,030
That's just Mata Hari
coming through,

511
00:33:08,197 --> 00:33:10,157
using whoever she can
to exact her revenge.

512
00:33:10,324 --> 00:33:13,785
But against who? The men who
put her to death are long gone.

513
00:33:13,952 --> 00:33:15,704
And besides, doesn't her real karma

514
00:33:15,871 --> 00:33:18,665
eventually lead to her own
self-destruction anyway?

515
00:33:18,874 --> 00:33:21,627
I think that's why we need to
figure out why she's using Phoebe

516
00:33:21,793 --> 00:33:23,170
before it's too late, right?

517
00:33:23,378 --> 00:33:25,839
Which brings us back
to Mata Hari's revenge.

518
00:33:26,131 --> 00:33:28,800
Okay, she spent
her life pleasing men,

519
00:33:28,967 --> 00:33:32,137
only to be betrayed
by them at the end.

520
00:33:33,222 --> 00:33:35,474
- Oh, no.
- What?

521
00:33:36,183 --> 00:33:38,727
What if she wants
to return the favour?

522
00:33:40,145 --> 00:33:42,606
- Mr. Dean.
- Mr. Dean.

523
00:33:43,232 --> 00:33:46,276
Just one quote. One quote, please.

524
00:33:47,277 --> 00:33:49,780
- What happened?
- What can you tell us about that?

525
00:33:50,239 --> 00:33:52,407
Listen up. I'll answer
at the press conference.

526
00:33:52,574 --> 00:33:56,495
Please do me a favour
and hold your questions until then.

527
00:33:58,330 --> 00:34:01,416
- Hello, Jason.
- Phoebe, I've had enough.

528
00:34:05,212 --> 00:34:09,550
- I always get my man.
- Wait, hang on a sec...

529
00:34:19,518 --> 00:34:22,271
I swear, this is where
we found the king last time.

530
00:34:22,437 --> 00:34:24,314
Well, maybe your orbing was off.

531
00:34:24,481 --> 00:34:27,901
My orbing was not off.
It just moved.

532
00:34:28,068 --> 00:34:31,613
Well, we should be hearing
the swarm, so why don't we?

533
00:34:31,780 --> 00:34:33,490
Because there's a jillion miles

534
00:34:33,657 --> 00:34:36,577
of this stupid maze.
They could be anywhere.

535
00:34:36,743 --> 00:34:39,037
We don't even know
if Phoebe is here.

536
00:34:39,204 --> 00:34:41,540
Well, it's our best bet.

537
00:34:41,707 --> 00:34:45,335
I swear, if she is hurt, I am
never going to forgive Richard.

538
00:34:45,502 --> 00:34:49,047
I think Jason's the one
we need to worry about right now.

539
00:34:56,054 --> 00:34:59,266
Such a sweet man.

540
00:34:59,433 --> 00:35:02,102
And such a horrible way to die.

541
00:35:02,895 --> 00:35:04,771
I almost want to cry.

542
00:35:04,938 --> 00:35:06,231
- Almost.
- What are you doing?

543
00:35:06,398 --> 00:35:07,900
Please stop this game.

544
00:35:08,108 --> 00:35:10,986
Life is a game.
The last one standing wins.

545
00:35:11,153 --> 00:35:12,779
- And that would be me.
- I get it.

546
00:35:12,988 --> 00:35:14,490
You're trying to teach me a lesson.

547
00:35:14,698 --> 00:35:15,908
No lesson.

548
00:35:16,074 --> 00:35:17,618
I just don't like being betrayed.

549
00:35:18,619 --> 00:35:20,787
Well, what about him,
won't he betray you?

550
00:35:22,331 --> 00:35:26,502
- Goodbye, mi amor.
- Phoebe, please. I'm begging you.

551
00:35:26,710 --> 00:35:29,713
Oh, don't beg.

552
00:35:29,880 --> 00:35:31,965
I stared at my killer right in the eye.

553
00:35:32,132 --> 00:35:34,760
It's a much more
dignified way to die.

554
00:35:35,719 --> 00:35:37,471
Richard was right.

555
00:35:37,679 --> 00:35:39,014
- Who?
- Enough!

556
00:35:39,640 --> 00:35:42,309
Can we please get on with this?

557
00:35:43,185 --> 00:35:44,895
Ready.

558
00:35:51,318 --> 00:35:52,486
Aim.

559
00:36:00,661 --> 00:36:01,995
No.

560
00:36:03,580 --> 00:36:05,040
Fire!

561
00:36:13,882 --> 00:36:16,301
Oh, thank God, I'm so happy
to see you guys.

562
00:36:16,468 --> 00:36:18,262
- You're you.
- Yeah.

563
00:36:18,428 --> 00:36:20,889
Okay, reunion later, slay now.

564
00:36:21,098 --> 00:36:23,392
Fire at her!

565
00:36:23,892 --> 00:36:25,686
"Demon swarm that serves as one

566
00:36:25,853 --> 00:36:28,105
Vanquish him from which they come"

567
00:36:34,653 --> 00:36:36,280
Jason.

568
00:36:38,282 --> 00:36:41,326
I'm so sorry. I'm so, so sorry.

569
00:36:41,493 --> 00:36:42,911
Me too.

570
00:36:43,078 --> 00:36:45,873
I hate to break this up,
I really do, but we gotta go.

571
00:36:46,039 --> 00:36:48,208
How did you get rid
of Mata Hari's karma?

572
00:36:49,126 --> 00:36:50,419
- Who?
- Don't ask.

573
00:36:50,627 --> 00:36:52,588
Where did you get the potion from?

574
00:36:52,754 --> 00:36:56,758
I got it from Richard, he said it would
be the only thing that might save you.

575
00:36:57,384 --> 00:36:59,094
Richard.

576
00:37:31,460 --> 00:37:33,587
- You okay?
- Oh, yeah, you know,

577
00:37:33,754 --> 00:37:37,382
considering I'm the mother
of the future leader of all evil.

578
00:37:37,549 --> 00:37:39,551
No, you're not.

579
00:37:40,052 --> 00:37:43,263
Okay, maybe he won't be, now that
you took care of the last threat on him.

580
00:37:43,430 --> 00:37:47,809
You know as well as I do that was not
the last threat. There'll be others.

581
00:37:47,976 --> 00:37:49,728
And you'll take care of them too.

582
00:37:49,895 --> 00:37:52,898
Especially now that we
know what can happen.

583
00:37:53,065 --> 00:37:55,734
After all, well aware is half there.

584
00:37:55,901 --> 00:37:58,320
Did Phoebe give you
that psychobabble?

585
00:38:00,739 --> 00:38:05,744
I just don't understand how someone
so sweet could possibly turn...

586
00:38:06,537 --> 00:38:08,580
...so bad.

587
00:38:08,789 --> 00:38:10,541
I don't believe he will.

588
00:38:10,707 --> 00:38:12,251
Despite what Chris says.

589
00:38:12,417 --> 00:38:15,671
Or, maybe because of it,
we won't let it.

590
00:38:16,547 --> 00:38:19,299
You know, Piper, all parents
worry about their kids.

591
00:38:19,466 --> 00:38:21,718
It's part of the job description.

592
00:38:22,052 --> 00:38:23,929
We just have to have faith.

593
00:38:24,137 --> 00:38:26,807
Yeah, but Wyatt isn't just any kid.

594
00:38:27,015 --> 00:38:30,269
And we're not just any parents either.

595
00:38:33,146 --> 00:38:36,525
Well, at least we know he'll
inherit all of our family's good karma.

596
00:38:36,692 --> 00:38:37,943
And that should help.

597
00:38:38,110 --> 00:38:39,570
I hope it helps Phoebe too.

598
00:38:39,736 --> 00:38:42,906
She still has what happened
at Jason's banquet to worry about.

599
00:38:45,617 --> 00:38:47,244
Mr. Dean.

600
00:38:48,537 --> 00:38:50,372
Here you are, sir.

601
00:38:53,667 --> 00:38:55,294
Jason!

602
00:38:55,460 --> 00:38:56,837
Jason!

603
00:38:57,004 --> 00:38:58,714
Phoebe?

604
00:39:02,259 --> 00:39:05,554
I want to talk to the press.
I want to tell them everything.

605
00:39:05,721 --> 00:39:07,681
What are you gonna do?
Tell them you're a witch?

606
00:39:07,848 --> 00:39:09,641
That'll make the headlines.

607
00:39:09,850 --> 00:39:12,978
Actually, I didn't think about
what I was gonna say to them.

608
00:39:13,145 --> 00:39:16,190
I just know that I can't let you
take the fall for this.

609
00:39:16,982 --> 00:39:18,692
I am so sorry.

610
00:39:18,859 --> 00:39:23,614
- About everything. The lies and...
- Hey.

611
00:39:23,906 --> 00:39:25,532
Don't.

612
00:39:25,741 --> 00:39:28,911
- Remember, you saved me.
- But that was after I tried to kill you.

613
00:39:29,077 --> 00:39:30,621
Well, there was that.

614
00:39:34,958 --> 00:39:37,753
If I could do it all again,

615
00:39:37,920 --> 00:39:39,463
I would tell you the truth.

616
00:39:39,671 --> 00:39:42,007
What are you gonna do,
what are you gonna tell me?

617
00:39:42,549 --> 00:39:44,301
And besides, I was...

618
00:39:44,468 --> 00:39:47,429
I was so wrapped up in my career
and dragging you around the world,

619
00:39:47,596 --> 00:39:49,389
I never gave you a chance.

620
00:39:52,184 --> 00:39:53,894
So...

621
00:39:56,063 --> 00:39:57,689
...what do we do now?

622
00:39:58,232 --> 00:39:59,942
I don't know.

623
00:40:01,819 --> 00:40:03,987
Maybe we should just...

624
00:40:06,073 --> 00:40:07,866
...both take some time.

625
00:40:14,206 --> 00:40:15,749
They're waiting for me.

626
00:40:18,210 --> 00:40:19,920
I wish you'd let me talk to them.

627
00:40:20,128 --> 00:40:23,048
No. No, what you
and your sisters do,

628
00:40:23,215 --> 00:40:25,717
what I saw you do...

629
00:40:25,884 --> 00:40:27,219
...it...

630
00:40:27,719 --> 00:40:30,472
...put some perspective
on my work.

631
00:40:31,139 --> 00:40:33,058
I want to protect that.

632
00:40:34,852 --> 00:40:37,062
You might lose the merger.

633
00:40:37,437 --> 00:40:38,981
I've lost worse.

634
00:41:10,387 --> 00:41:12,181
Mr. Dean!

